# Shop upgrades UI — no unsolicited visual changes

The creator **Shop Upgrades** page (`/dashboard/shop-upgrades`) and its UI are layout-approved.

**Do not change formatting, styling, layout, spacing, copy, or visual structure** on this surface unless the user **explicitly requests** that visual change in the current conversation.

## In scope (treat the same as the page)

- `src/app/dashboard/shop-upgrades/**`
- `src/components/dashboard/promotions/**`
- `src/components/dashboard/Promotions*.tsx`, `Promotion*.tsx`
- `src/components/dashboard/ShopFlairSection.tsx`
- `src/components/dashboard/ShopGoogleShoppingSection.tsx`
- `src/components/dashboard/PromotionsSectionFrame.tsx`
- Related display helpers when the task is only about this page’s appearance (e.g. `promotion-checkout-period-display.ts`, period picker fieldset)

## Allowed without an explicit visual request

- Bug fixes that restore **documented/intended** behavior (broken checkout, wrong price math, failed payment)
- Wiring, data fetching, server actions, types, performance — **only if** the diff does not alter how the page looks
- Changes the user asked for in non-visual terms (e.g. “inline pay instead of redirect”) — minimize CSS/class churn; do not opportunistically restyle adjacent UI

## Requires explicit user ask

- Tailwind classes, grid/flex layout, column widths, alignment
- Labels, button text, section order, borders, colors, spacing
- Refactors whose primary effect is visual (even if “cleaner”)

When unsure whether a change affects appearance, **ask first** or keep the existing markup and classes.
